<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1987-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Antiviral Chemotherapyand Prophylaxis of Viral Respiratory Disease</TITLE><BODY>Several antiviral agents are currently available for the treatment and prophylaxis of viral respiratory disease. These include oral amantadine for influenza A and aerosolized ribavirin for respiratory syncytial virus infections. Additional agents, such as rimantadine and intranasal interferons, and newer approaches, including th–µ use of combination chemotherapy, offer promise for the improved management of viral respiratory tract infections.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>